22. Generate Parentheses
Medium

5518

278

Add to List

Share
Given n pairs of parentheses, write a function to generate all combinations of well-formed parentheses.

For example, given n = 3, a solution set is:

[
  "((()))",
  "(()())",
  "(())()",
  "()(())",
  "()()()"
]



The idea here is to only add '(' and ')' that we know will guarantee us a solution (instead of adding 1 too many close). Once 
we add a '(' we will then discard it and try a ')' which can only close a valid '('. Each 
of these steps are recursively called.


class Solution {
public:
    vector<string> generateParenthesis(int n) {
        vector<string> res;
        addingpar(res, "", n, 0);
        return res;
    }
    void addingpar(vector<string> &v, string str, int n, int m){
        if(n==0 && m==0) {
            v.push_back(str);
            return;
        }
        if(m > 0){ addingpar(v, str+")", n, m-1); }
        if(n > 0){ addingpar(v, str+"(", n-1, m+1); }
    }
};
